stories.text:
Hello all!

Last year we decided to open our internal DevOps workshops to everyone and we had our first DevOps League event, which was a big success (unfortunately it was in Greek, but still a big success!)

This time around we decided to go global (all presentations will be in English), go bigger (4 different companies will participate) and explore the exciting ecosystem of Terraform in a ~5h event. We'll start small with the foundations and work ourselves to the top in terms of complexity and best practises.

If you want to join us on 22th of November, feel free to register at https://globalwebindex.zoom.us/webinar/register/9516366272258/WN_SgkXTQZdSlmM5R50295S-A or spread the word if you know anyone who might be interested. Attendance is free, and the whole event is a labor of love from various DevOps in different companies.
